-- Merck to Cut 800 Jobs in France After Schering Purchase, La Tribune Says
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-06-17T04:42:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/merck-to-cut-800-jobs-in-france-after-schering-purchase-la-tribune-says.html

          
          
             Merck & Co. plans to cut about 800
jobs in France, or 20 percent of its workforce in the country,
following its purchase of Schering-Plough last year, French
daily La Tribune reported, citing management and unions.  
 Medical visitors will bear the brunt of the job cuts,
according to the newspaper.  
          
          


  


        